# Classification on Stroke Dataset Using Machine Learning

## About the Files
The `main.py` file contains all the plots in Python. The `Image` folder contains output images from the code, like bar charts.
The `preprocess.py` file contains all the preprocessing steps in Python. The `preorocess` folder contains the output files in xlxs.
The `run_algorithms.py` file is used to run different Machine Learning algorithms on the data to see what steps in preprocessing gives better results.
The `smote.py` file contains the proposed method for stroke classification.

## The Steps
This project is a machine learning project on the Stroke dataset.  
- First, functions help us understand the data better.  
- Next, we handle outliers and missing values and then normalize the data.  
- Next, different Machine Learning algorithms are run on datasets.
- At last, the proposed method is introduced.

## About the Dataset
The stroke dataset consists of 5110 records of patients with various attributes. The target feature is `stroke`, and other features include `age`, `gender`, `work_type`, and more. 
This dataset is widely used in classification tasks, and many papers have used it to build classifiers.

## Dataset link: 
[Stroke Prediction Dataset on Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/fedesoriano/stroke-prediction-dataset/data)
